wer is CD, but how can this be when we share it with two other classes? that some how Charge is another class definer, but again if you can buy at the trainers shop how can that make it unique? We can train in CD but it does not add damage or speed to the attack, (I remember something about a &quot;Blur of Steel&quot;, no laughing, chuckles are permitted). Comments about Riposte to add to our parry would be wonderful. I wonder sometimes about the very name of BLADEmaster when only those of the Purest heart stay with Blades and have not become a BLUNTmaster (which I have become, a most happy member), I bow to the pureity of those that swing the sword. I would love to be able to use all those wonderful attacks in RVR battles instead of my one, and of course the Flurry that I may use every two minutes (will an egg timer be useful?), however this is not possible due too the fact that I hardly ever parry (my parry is set to 44 with +8 total 52), and add to that the frustration of anything (possibly even the frogs croaking) interrupting my swing concentration and then I will simply swing for ugh 60 to 70 something with my right mace and 40-50 something with the left (er.... sometimes with the left). I am not crying or bemoaning our situation simply saying that we with the fixing of Styles damage, interuption, meaningless styles ( I mean when do you hit from the side in RVR?, and only when your trying to chase down the hapeless last man standing will you even think &quot;hey if i switch to quick bar 7 for RVE i can use a back attack here&quot;). I also now having read the what I believe shall become the Imfamous 1.53f patch, in which now Middies will be doing even more Magical damage (see Kentucky Fried Blade/Bluntmaster). I am I the only one that, fears/loathes casters possibly as much as the casters feared/loathed Rangers? until the First Great Nerf came from on high, creating the new Age &quot;The Great Age of Casters&quot;. I mean really would you or any other class even imagine tring to level in the CF without at least 2 or 1 great one in your group? the only time I like to see one. So now we face this kind of damage ourselves in RVR, do we then nerf casters or give us trench fighters greater hit points (that too can be bought), or perhaps some greater resistance to magic ( can I buy that too?) I mean really what am i suppose to do? I really dont like to be mez/stun/rooted so I buy purge/Avoidance of Magic/Determination. and in the mean time as a bounce from bar to bar I am being slapped like new babies, well you know what I mean. So just what Realm R ank do I need to be? So please don't stick a fork in me and call me done because that is what every caster in Albion is doing and soon Midgard will be doing too. I simply ask to be able to go into battle (with a Sword or two raised high, not a mace), with some reasurrance that I might last longer than my Triple Wield.<br>
